column5: Lots of people say dog lake is fished out, I say you are nuts!http://ontariofishingcommunity.com/f...howtopic=58011 It was a great week

Dog lake can be tough at times, but it can be spectacular at times too. Last visit stayed at Island View camps on the east end of the lake. Didn't get out of the camps view and fished around the island and the four of us caught 100 walleyes a day. It was like perch fishing action. The lake is huge and the walleyes generally are concentrated.
